==English==

===Etymology===
From Esperanto ''esperantisto'' (an Esperanto Expert or Proponent), which derives from the Esperanto word ''Esperanto''. The suffix ''ist'' means ''connected with'' or ''habitually ocupied with'' or ''specialist in''. When this suffix is added  to the radical ''esperant'', the new word ''esperantisto'' means ''someone who is a specialist in Esperanto''. 

